<LP>
   WAYNE, N.J. -- Reckitt &amp; Colman Inc. said it plans to sell
three of its household carpet and upholstery cleaners,
marketed under the Glamorene brand name.
   Reckitt, a subsidiary of Reckitt &amp; Colman PLC, London,
said it entered into a consent order with the Federal Trade
Commission to sell its Spray 'n Vac, Spray 'n Brush and Apply
'n Vac brands of carpet and upholstery cleaners.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Reckitt recently acquired the Boyle-Midway household
products division of American Home Products Corp., for about
$1.25 billion; the business includes the Woolite brand of
carpet cleaning products.
   TM Capital Corp., a New York investment banking firm, was
retained by Reckitt &amp; Colman to assist in the planned
divestiture.
